On PTSD Awareness Day, the article highlights the importance of recognizing and improving treatment options for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD). It states that approximately 8% of Americans, including children and adolescents who have experienced abuse and trauma, suffer from PTSD. The article emphasizes the administration's commitment to improving access to mental healthcare for all Americans. Additionally, it acknowledges the impact of PTSD on veterans and emphasizes the need for them to receive world-class healthcare. The article mentions the signing of the Veterans Choice Program Improvement Act, which extends and improves the Veterans Choice Program, allowing eligible veterans to choose their own doctors for treatment. Ultimately, the article commits to helping fellow Americans be free from the suffering of PTSD and enjoy the blessings of the nation.